we can deploy application to production using devops flow , k8s etc why MLops needed?
Machine Learning is different from normal software because models learn from data and their performance can change over time.
So ML systems follow a Model Lifecycle to ensure the model is trained, validated, deployed, and continuously improved.
_____________________
interview answer
1.MLOps:
“MLOps (Machine Learning Operations) is the practice of applying DevOps principles like CI/CD, automation, and monitoring to the machine learning lifecycle.
It manages the end-to-end process of data preparation, model training, versioning, deployment, and monitoring. 
The goal is to reliably deploy ML models into production and continuously improve them as data and performance change.”

role---mlops
“From a DevOps/SRE perspective, my role in MLOps was mainly around building and maintaining the infrastructure and automation pipelines. 
This included containerizing ML workloads using Docker, deploying model services on Kubernetes, integrating experiment tracking tools like MLflow,
and implementing CI/CD pipelines with Jenkins and ArgoCD to automate model deployment and version upgrades.”
